Compressing A PNG image.
pngcrush -ow image.png

Compressing all PNG images whose name contains "223 - Average 1" and end by ".png".
for file in "223 - Average 1"*.png; do pngcrush -ow "$file"; done

Compressing all MP4 videos whose name begins by "75".
find . -maxdepth 1 -type f -name '75*.mp4'  -exec sh -c 'ffmpeg -y -i "$1" -c:v libx264 -crf 23 -c:a aac -b:a 128k "${1%.mp4}_compressed.mp4"' sh {} \;

Compressing all PNG images whose size is greater than 16 Mo.
find . -maxdepth 1 -type f -name '*.png' -size +16M -exec pngcrush -ow {} \;

Getting the number of frames in the file "video"
ffprobe -v error -count_frames -select_streams v:0 -show_entries stream=nb_read_frames -of csv=p=0 video.mp4

Listing the subfolders of "Input" and "Output"
for dir in Input Output; do echo "=== $dir ==="; tree -d "$dir"; echo; done

Deleting all files in a folder (subfolders included).
find . -type f -delete

Listing files whose name begis by 623 and contains "rage 0" and " 1.00-" | Display the number of files.
find . -type f -name "623*rage 0* 1.00-*" | awk '{print; c++} END{print c " files"}'

Listing unique filenames in the "One Color" folder by cutting after "- Tolerance". Delete "Output/One Color" to run in the current folder.
find "Output/One Color" -type f   -printf '%f\n' | sed 's/ - Tolerance.*//' | sort -u

Listing unique filenames whose name contains "CN 40" | display names truncated from "TB".
find -type f -name "*CN 40*" -printf '%f\n' | sed 's/TB.*//' | sort -u

Listing the 20 largest files (useful to launch in the "Output" folder if processing time is getting important).
find . -type f -exec du -h {} + | sort --human-numeric-sort --reverse | head -n 20

Listing MP4 files, including subfolders
find . -type f \( -iname "*.mp4" \) -printf "%P\n"

Renaming all files whose name begin by "ABC-" to delete the first 4 characters ("ABC-" is for the example).
for f in "ABC-"*; do   mv "$f" "${f#ABC-}"; done
